# Tanya Mehra | Day 7 ## Daily Notes 1. Indie Web: Non Corporate Website ( Personal ) 2. Its principal 3. Talked about Owning your data 4. Hosting your Data, - Own Domain Name ( Eating Your Design) **"Creating your home cooked meal" - NO DEPENDENSE (Become Self Sufficient)** 5. Open Source : Everybody can look to it and is available to all. 6. Timeline: Every dot is interconnected and it's something depend on us how we want to organize it. **"At the end it's about creating your own space in your own way".** 7. From all the given links; - Digital Gardening: Which i guess is the best way to explain it to anyone to why one should be on the web and how t is structured. - It's like planting a seed now till it grows up and become more stronger with years. 8. I really like how people use their own space to organize them self and there interest, hobbies and even travelling. I mean it's like your very own a life tracker. ## Work update 1. Brainstormed about what i want in my final project 2. ### Assignment ( Manifesto ) **This is my space to create, learn, and grow, Here I share my work, ideas, and journey, unfiltered and always evolving.** I want to curate my own space which will have my **life showcase** - **written articles**, **My to do lists** ( year/month/day) with the progress, **My current happening** - what i am doing right now, **my work - both design and research**, **cafe hopping at it's review**, also **my hobby column** ( I want to organize this in fun and interactive way) I want to make it a WOW! for me and for anyone who looks at it and knows me can tell that Yaaaaaa its Tanya's space.(I will use text ,images and writeups along with illustrations - But Layout ill figure it out by tomorrow! ## Answer to the BONUS Question: I feel It's ovio that we have such small period of time so we can't just keep learning the application ( It's Something we'll do it by practice and time ) But at the end result When we are saying **Immersive** ( completely involved in something) **Web Design** It should feel like we have something of our own. and I am sure that i would really want to use this knowledge further professionally and as well as personally so that I can code my own work and publish it my self anytime. ( Brain storming Image)
